==English==
=== Etymology ===
From the Italian ''[[innamorata]]'', the feminine form of ''[[innamorato]]'', from ''[[innamorare]]'' "to fall in love," from ''[[in-]]'' "in" + ''[[amore]]'' "love"

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɑːtə|-ɑːtə]]

=== Noun ===
'''inamorata'''
# a [[female]] [[lover]] or [[love]] [[interest]]

